US-based Nigerian music artist Ebere Mbadi aka Jaajo, has released a seven-track Extended Play (EP) titled ‘Afrolypso’. According to Jaajo, the seven-track EP was produced to serenade Africans and those in Black communities on a global scale. The songs on the EP include Lovu Lovu, Oyogo, Out of my way, Rollam, Control, Yolo, and Joro Joro’. Speaking about the project and what each song entails, Jaajo explained that the theme of the body of work is centered around Africans and their musical tastes.   Hydro explains reason for rebranding     Brymo thrills fans at Sing Along Tour     Obi Cubana, wife celebrate 14th wedding anniversary   “Listening to this project, you will have a feel of local-oriented beats, and African cultural infusion,” he stated. “Lovu Lovu was inspired by a love gone wrong while Oyogo was inspired by a tale of a pretty young girl in a local part of the country,” he stated. Unlike Lovu Lovu and Oyogo, Out of my Way, according to Jaajo, is a testimonial song. The talented music star added that Rollam is inspired by traditional female dancers while Control is inspired by a pretty damsel whose beauty can even make the most powerful man on earth to lose control.